t. Providing a new perspective on our nation’s current dilemmas, Smith also offers hope for change through an embrace of authentic history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCold WarxHistoriography. 0aNational characteristics, American. 0aSpanish-American War, 1898xHistoriography. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009xHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030017656840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019529340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300195293423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300195293/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY